                            <comment id="16442477" author="juliuszsompolski" created="Wed, 18 Apr 2018 13:15:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This hits when trying to create histogram statistics (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-21975&quot; title=&quot;Histogram support in cost-based optimizer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-21975&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-21975&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) on columns like monotonically increasing id - histograms cannot be created in reasonable time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16448058" author="mgaido" created="Mon, 23 Apr 2018 12:29:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I cannot reproduce on current master. For me it was very fast the second query too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16448093" author="juliuszsompolski" created="Mon, 23 Apr 2018 12:51:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mgaido&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mgaido&quot;&gt;mgaido&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
I tested again on current master (afbdf427302aba858f95205ecef7667f412b2a6a) and I reproduce it:&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12920281/12920281_screenshot-1.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe you need to bump up 10000000 to something higher when running on a bigger cluster that splits the range into more tasks?&lt;br/&gt;
For me it grinds to a halt after about 2500000 per task.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16448365" author="mgaido" created="Mon, 23 Apr 2018 16:09:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=juliuszsompolski&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;juliuszsompolski&quot;&gt;juliuszsompolski&lt;/a&gt; I have been able to reproduce with 10000000. Probably &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-17439&quot; title=&quot;QuantilesSummaries returns the wrong result after compression&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-17439&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-17439&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is related. The problem is that the compress method is called too many times in this condition. The fix is easy, I&apos;ll submit a patch soon, but I am not so familiar with this algorithm and the real root cause of the problem, so I have to study it a bit in order to check if there are other problems causing the performance issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16448854" author="apachespark" created="Mon, 23 Apr 2018 20:53:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;mgaido91&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/21133&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/21133&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
